description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Practitioners x 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MH, LD, A &amp; CAMHS Commissioning Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Type: Full Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed term or secondment (Secondment considered with employers permission)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Lincolnshire Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) is committed to involving patients, the public, partners and key stakeholders in the development of future services, identifying priorities and understanding the needs of our population. We aim to improve local health services and respond to the health needs of everyone in the area by ensuring patients and the public are at the heart of the entire decision making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit 2 dynamic patient centred Assistant Practitioners to work for  Lincolnshire CCG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is an exciting time to join us and help shape our response to the Transforming Care programme, the Mental Health forward view and changes to service provision. The role of the 2 Assistant Practitioners is to; support our 3 Expert by Experience workers to ensure that health services are delivered in line with the Transforming Care programme and to support the work streams undertaken by The Operational Commissioning Team; Care and Treatment Reviews, Continuing Health Care, Mental Health and Out Area Placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to hold NVQ level 2/3/ A Level qualifications/Health and Social Care or equivalent experiences in service area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered as a fixed term or secondment, 37.5 hours a week, over 5 days Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Julie Betts for more information on 07920 710 508 or email  julie.betts@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date – 06/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date- 19/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
